profile:
Susan founded happy pea in 2013 after a long career in the Investment Industry. When working through potential company names she was struck both by the perfect design of a pea pod that allows it to hold the peas, and nothing else, and the fact that no one can say “happy” without smiling. Susan knew that she’d often be helping clients deal with less than happy situations, so, happy pea was born. It still makes her smile.
 
You can expect:
 
Guidance and direction in making difficult decisions
Support and practical solutions
Discreet and non-judging atmosphere
About The Professional Organizer.
Susan Hammond is a Trained Professional Organizer, and a member of Professional Organizers in Canada. Along with earning a Certificate of Study in Understanding the Needs of the Aging Chronically Disorganized Client, she has received her Hoarding, CD and ADHD Specialist Certificate from the Institute for Challenging Organization.
 
She loves coaching overwhelmed clients to stop worrying about the forest and just deal with one tree at a time.
 
A two time Ironman finisher who still loves to swim, bike, and run, Susan brings energy, humour and focus to every project she takes on.
 
Susan is very involved in her association, Professional Organizers in Canada, serving as Chair on the Toronto Chapter Board.
name: Happy Pea
